In article <931111.72363.BOBES_PIERRE@delphi.com>, BOBES_PIERRE@delphi.com writes:
> I have been reading and educating myself with references from this forum
> and other ftp sites. It is apparent however that my remedial level of math
> skills (algebra in high school, one year of calculus in college years ago)
> are limiting my horizons. Any suggestions of texts that "walk" you thru
> the math or teach it in an organized fashion as related to cryptology?
> If not, any suggestions of math texts to start on?
> thanks
> bob mintz

You might want to read 'A Course in Number Theory and Cryptography' by
Koblitz (Springer Verlag). Almost all algebra needed for the algorithms in
the book can be found in the first chapters of the book.

